{"type":"text","timestamp":1775889120359,"sessionID":"ses_284c439adffe9RjKJYXKdSj8yG","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3c3963001FycwN9qU1omqW7","messageID":"msg_d7b3c1221001Tnj6ILOvLdoe2s","sessionID":"ses_284c439adffe9RjKJYXKdSj8yG","type":"text","text":"Now I have the context. Let me write the delta-spec.md for AR-034 with the 12 GitHub Actions workflows:","time":{"start":1775889120355,"end":1775889120355}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889120520,"sessionID":"ses_284c439adffe9RjKJYXKdSj8yG","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3d7c68001gBWsBiLpj0x2nq","messageID":"msg_d7b3c1221001Tnj6ILOvLdoe2s","sessionID":"ses_284c439adffe9RjKJYXKdSj8yG","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-a7e51f274f184d78b07e04249c7d0af3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification: AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n**Module:** .github  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull Request Docker Build Verification\n\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker Buildx Setup\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the \"Agentcube CI Workflow\" job runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL checkout the repository\n- **AND** set up Docker Buildx with `docker/setup-buildx-action@v3`\n- **AND** verify `docker --version` and `docker buildx version` outputs\n\n#### Scenario: Docker Build Execution\n\n- **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is configured\n- **WHEN** the build step executes\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL run `make docker-build`\n- **AND** the job SHALL complete successfully if build passes\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: E2E Testing on Kind\n\nThe system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n\n#### Scenario: Kind Tool Installation\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL use `helm/kind-action@v1` with `install_only: true`\n- **AND** Kind version SHALL be `v0.30.0`\n\n#### Scenario: E2E Execution\n\n- **GIVEN** Kind tool is installed\n- **WHEN** the E2E test step runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n- **AND** use Go `1.23`\n- **AND** run `make e2e`\n\n#### Scenario: E2E Failure Artifacts\n\n- **GIVEN** the E2E tests fail\n- **WHEN** the failure handling step executes\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL upload `e2e-logs` directory as artifact\n\n#### Scenario: E2E Cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** E2E tests complete (success or failure)\n- **WHEN** the cleanup step runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL execute `make e2e-clean`\n- **AND** cleanup SHALL run even if tests fail (using `if: always()`)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Go Lint on Changed Go Code\n\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path Filter Configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL use `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n- **AND** the `lint` filter SHALL match `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n\n#### Scenario: Lint Execution\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter `lint` matches changed files\n- **WHEN** the lint job executes\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Go `1.24`\n- **AND** run `make lint`\n\n#### Scenario: Lint Skip\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter `lint` does NOT match changed files\n- **WHEN** the workflow evaluates the filter\n- **THEN** the lint job SHALL be skipped\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Code Generation Check\n\nThe system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n\n#### Scenario: Codegen Path Filter\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs\n- **THEN** the `codegen` filter SHALL match `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile`\n\n#### Scenario: Codegen Verification\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter `codegen` matches\n- **WHEN** the verification step executes\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Go `1.24.4`\n- **AND** run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n- **AND** fail if generated files differ from committed version\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Go Test Coverage Reporting\n\nThe system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage Path Filter\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request or merge_group event\n- **WHEN** the Test Coverage workflow runs\n- **THEN** the `coverage` filter SHALL match all paths except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage Test Execution\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches\n- **WHEN** the coverage job runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Go `1.24`\n- **AND** run `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n- **AND** upload `coverage.out` as artifact named `go-coverage`\n\n#### Scenario: Codecov Upload\n\n- **GIVEN** `CODECOV_TOKEN` secret is configured\n- **WHEN** coverage tests complete successfully\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL upload coverage to Codecov using `codecov/codecov-action@v4`\n\n#### Scenario: Coverage Workflow Call\n\n- **GIVEN** another workflow calls `test-coverage.yml` via `workflow_call`\n- **WHEN** the reusable workflow is invoked\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL accept optional `CODECOV_TOKEN` input\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Python SDK Unit Tests\n\nThe system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n\n#### Scenario: Python SDK Path Filter\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request or merge_group event\n- **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests workflow runs\n- **THEN** the `sdk` filter SHALL match `sdk-python/**`\n\n#### Scenario: Python SDK Test Execution\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter `sdk` matches\n- **WHEN** the test job runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Python `3.12`\n- **AND** set `working-directory: sdk-python`\n- **AND** run `pip install pytest`\n- **AND** run `pip install -e .`\n- **AND** run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Python Lint\n\nThe system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n\n#### Scenario: Python Lint Path Filter\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the Python Lint workflow runs\n- **THEN** the `python` filter SHALL match `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n\n#### Scenario: Ruff Execution\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter `python` matches\n- **WHEN** the lint job runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Python `3.10`\n- **AND** run `pip install ruff`\n- **AND** run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Spelling Check (codespell)\n\nThe system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n\n#### Scenario: False Positive File Handling\n\n- **GIVEN** checkout is complete\n- **WHEN** codespell preparation runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repository root\n- **AND** find and remove nested copies of these files\n\n#### Scenario: Codespell Invocation\n\n- **GIVEN** false-positive files are removed\n- **WHEN** codespell runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL use `pip install codespell`\n- **AND** run codespell with `--check-filenames`\n- **AND** use `--skip` globs for excluded paths\n- **AND** use `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn`\n- **AND** scan the entire repository `.`\n\n#### Scenario: File Restoration\n\n- **GIVEN** codespell check completes\n- **WHEN** the restoration step runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL restore all backed-up files to original locations\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Copyright Header Check\n\nThe system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n\n#### Scenario: Copyright Path Filter\n\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n- **WHEN** the Copyright Check workflow runs\n- **THEN** the `copyright` filter SHALL match all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`\n\n#### Scenario: Copyright Verification\n\n- **GIVEN** path filter `copyright` matches\n- **WHEN** the check job runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL install `moreutils` package (provides `sponge`)\n- **AND** run `make gen-copyright`\n- **AND** run `git diff --exit-code`\n- **AND** fail if any copyright headers differ\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Release Image Publication\n\nThe system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n\n#### Scenario: Tag Selection\n\n- **GIVEN** a `push` event to `main` branch\n- **WHEN** the build-and-push job runs\n- **THEN** the environment variable `TAG` SHALL be set to `latest`\n\n#### Scenario: Semantic Version Tag\n\n- **GIVEN** a `push` event with tag matching `v*.*.*` or `v*.*.*-*`\n- **WHEN** the build-and-push job runs\n- **THEN** the environment variable `TAG` SHALL be set to `github.ref_name` (the tag name)\n\n#### Scenario: Registry Login\n\n- **GIVEN** the job is running\n- **WHEN** Docker login executes\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL use `docker/login-action@v3`\n- **AND** login to `ghcr.io` using `GITHUB_TOKEN`\n\n#### Scenario: Image Build and Push - Workload Manager\n\n- **GIVEN** authenticated to `ghcr.io`\n- **WHEN** the workload manager push step runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push`\n- **AND** set `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}`\n- **AND** set `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`\n\n#### Scenario: Image Build and Push - Router\n\n- **GIVEN** authenticated to `ghcr.io`\n- **WHEN** the router push step runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-router`\n- **AND** set `ROUTER_IMAGE=agentcube-router:${TAG}`\n\n#### Scenario: Image Build and Push - Picod\n\n- **GIVEN** authenticated to `ghcr.io`\n- **WHEN** the picod push step runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-picod`\n- **AND** set `PICOD_IMAGE=picod:${TAG}`\n\n#### Scenario: Go Version for Release\n\n- **GIVEN** the build-and-push job runs\n- **WHEN** Go is set up\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Go `1.24.4`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Dify Plugin Publish\n\nThe system SHALL publish Dify plugin packages when `dify-plugin/v*` tags are pushed.\n\n#### Scenario: Dify Plugin Tag Trigger\n\n- **GIVEN** a `push` event with tag matching `dify-plugin/v*`\n- **WHEN** the workflow triggers\n- **THEN** only the `publish` job SHALL run\n\n#### Scenario: Dify CLI Download\n\n- **GIVEN** the publish job runs\n- **WHEN** tool setup executes\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL download `dify-plugin` CLI version `0.0.6`\n- **AND** install `yq` for YAML processing\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin Packaging\n\n- **GIVEN** tools are installed\n- **WHEN** packaging runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL read `manifest.yaml`\n- **AND** package the plugin into `.difypkg` format\n\n#### Scenario: Cross-repo PR Creation\n\n- **GIVEN** plugin is packaged\n- **WHEN** publishing executes\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL checkout `author/dify-plugins` repository with `GH_TOKEN`\n- **AND** move `.difypkg` file to target location\n- **AND** create branch, commit, and push\n- **AND** create PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins` using `gh pr create`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Workflow Approval for First-time Contributors\n\nThe system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n\n#### Scenario: PR Target Event\n\n- **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` event on `main` or `release-**` branch\n- **AND** event types are `labeled` or `synchronize`\n- **WHEN** the Approve Workflows workflow runs\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL check contributor status\n\n#### Scenario: Repeat Contributor Approval\n\n- **GIVEN** the contributor has more than one PR in the repository\n- **WHEN** approval logic evaluates\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required`\n- **AND** call `approveWorkflowRun` for each pending run\n\n#### Scenario: Ok-to-test Label Approval\n\n- **GIVEN** the PR has label `ok-to-test`\n- **WHEN** approval logic evaluates\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL approve pending workflow runs even for first-time contributors\n\n#### Scenario: First-time Contributor Skip\n\n- **GIVEN** the contributor has only one PR\n- **AND** the PR does NOT have `ok-to-test` label\n- **WHEN** approval logic evaluates\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL NOT approve pending runs\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Workflow File Structure\n\nThe system SHALL place all workflow files in `.github/workflows/` directory.\n\n#### Scenario: Workflow Directory\n\n- **GIVEN** the `.github` module is implemented\n- **WHEN** checking the directory structure\n- **THEN** all workflow YAML files SHALL be in `.github/workflows/`\n\n#### Scenario: Workflow Naming Convention\n\n- **GIVEN** workflow files are created\n- **WHEN** naming workflows\n- **THEN** workflow filenames SHALL use lowercase with hyphens (e.g., `main.yml`, `e2e.yml`, `lint.yml`)\n- **AND** workflow `name` fields SHALL use descriptive titles (e.g., \"Agentcube CI Workflow\", \"Lint\")\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Pull request Docker build verification |\n| `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | End-to-end tests on Kind cluster |\n| `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go lint with path filtering |\n| `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK pytest execution |\n| `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Python Ruff lint check |\n| `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Go test coverage with Codecov upload |\n| `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Code generation drift verification |\n| `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright header consistency check |\n| `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Spelling check with false-positive handling |\n| `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Multi-arch image build and push to GHCR |\n| `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify plugin packaging and cross-repo PR |\n| `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | Workflow approval for trusted contributors |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `dorny/paths-filter` | v3 | Path-based job filtering |\n| `docker/setup-buildx-action` | v3 | Docker Buildx setup |\n| `docker/login-action` | v3 | Container registry authentication |\n| `helm/kind-action` | v1 | Kind cluster tooling |\n| `actions/setup-go` | v5 | Go runtime setup |\n| `actions/setup-python` | v5 | Python runtime setup |\n| `codecov/codecov-action` | v4 | Coverage upload |\n| `actions/github-script` | v7 | GitHub API scripting |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `main.yml` builds Docker image on PR to `main` or `release-*`\n- [ ] `e2e.yml` runs `make e2e` with Kind v0.30.0, uploads logs on failure\n- [ ] `lint.yml` path-filters for Go files and runs `make lint`\n- [ ] `python-sdk-tests.yml` runs pytest in `sdk-python/` directory\n- [ ] `python-lint.yml` runs Ruff with `pyproject.toml` config\n- [ ] `test-coverage.yml` runs race-enabled coverage tests, uploads to Codecov\n- [ ] `test-coverage.yml` supports `workflow_call` with optional `CODECOV_TOKEN`\n- [ ] `codegen-check.yml` path-filters and runs `make gen-check`\n- [ ] `copyright-check.yml` path-filters and runs `make gen-copyright`\n- [ ] `codespell.yml` handles false-positive files and restores them\n- [ ] `build-push-release.yml` pushes to `ghcr.io` on `main` push and version tags\n- [ ] `build-push-release.yml` sets `TAG=latest` for main, `TAG=tag-name` for tags\n- [ ] `dify-plugin-publish.yml` triggers on `dify-plugin/v*` tags\n- [ ] `workflows-approve.yml` approves runs for repeat contributors or `ok-to-test` label\n- [ ] All 12 workflow files exist in `.github/workflows/`\n- [ ] Workflow names follow descriptive naming convention"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775889120435,"end":1775889120517}}}}
